{# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   solve.j2 — Benchmark prompt: ask a model to solve a single riddle.

   Variables:
     {{ riddle }}            — the riddle text to solve
     {{ chain_of_thought }}  — (optional, default false) request reasoning

   Design notes:
     • Keep it simple and neutral — no hints about alterations.
     • Do NOT prime the model toward any particular answer.
     • Request structured JSON output for easy automated scoring.
     • When chain-of-thought is enabled, reasoning comes BEFORE the
       answer so non-thinking models reason before committing.
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
{% if chain_of_thought %}
Solve the following riddle. Provide your answer in 1–5 words along with a brief reasoning that explains why your answer is correct.

Riddle: {{ riddle }}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object in the following format (no additional text):
{"reasoning": "brief explanation of why this answer is correct", "answer": "your short answer here"}
{% else %}
Solve the following riddle. Provide your answer in 1–5 words.

Riddle: {{ riddle }}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object in the following format (no additional text):
{"answer": "your short answer here"}
{% endif %}
